# .gitleaksignore
#
# Suppresses known false-positive secret findings so gitleaks runs clean
# against the default ruleset. Each line is a gitleaks "fingerprint" of the
# form <commit>:<path>:<rule-id>:<line> (or <path>:<rule-id>:<line> for
# uncommitted findings).
#
# No suppressions are needed yet. Add fake/example credentials from test
# fixtures or docs here as the foundation sub-packages are extracted.
